S T A T E O F R H O D E I S L A N D
IN GENERAL ASSEMBLY
JANUARY SESSION, A.D. 2025
____________
H O U S E R E S O L U T I O N
AMENDING THE RULES OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES FOR THE YEARS
2023-2024
Introduced By: Representative Brian C. Newberry
Date Introduced: January 10, 2025
Referred To: House Rules
1 RESOLVED, That the rules of the House of Representatives adopted by the House of
2 Representatives at its January session, A.D. 2023, entitled "House Resolution Adopting Rules of
3 the House of Representatives for the years 2023 and 2024", be and the same is hereby amended
4 by adding the following new rule thereto:
5 Legislative Grants
6 (49) All appropriations of legislative grants contained in the budget bill shall be divided
7 and appropriated by amount between the Senate and the House of Representatives. Any amount
8 of legislative grants appropriated and allocated to the Senate shall be distributed in accordance
9 with Senate rules or another method adopted by the Senate.
10 Any amounts of legislative grants appropriated and allocated to the House of
11 Representative shall be equally divided among the seventy-five (75) legislative districts, and the
12 budget bill shall provide that each member may direct the distribution of the legislative grant
13 intended for the district which such member represents by written communication to the Speaker
14 of the House between July 1 and September 30 of each budget year.
